\begin_layout Subsubsection
Ultrafast entanglement gate with state-dependent momentum kick
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The frame work of the ultrafast gate is first proposed by Cirac and Zoller
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "garcia2003speed"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 with many tries to realized in experiments
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "mizrahi2014quantum,johnson2017ultrafast,ratcliffe2018scaling,ratcliffe2019micromotion"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Here we try to give a feasible scheme with the ARP pulse mentioned above.
 The key is we propose to use the fast AWG modulated CW laser instead of
 pulse laser ,which get rid of the problem of reputation rate.
 So the sequence time and phase control could be more flexible and precise.
 The basic idea is that the operation is faster than the trap frequency
 so the ions get a big momentum transfer without moving.
 If we consider the simple case: we have two ions and both irradiated by
 the bi-chromatic light with the same intensity (same effective Rabi frequency
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega_{eff}(t)$
\end_inset

 ) and single ion addressing.
 The Hamilton can be written as: 
\begin_inset Formula $H=H_{m}+H_{I}$
\end_inset

, where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
H_{m} & =\hbar\omega_{c}a_{c}^{+}a_{c}+\hbar\omega_{s}a_{s}^{+}a_{s},\nonumber \\
H_{I} & =\hbar\frac{\Omega_{eff}(t)}{2}(\sigma_{1}^{+}e^{2ikx_{1}}+\sigma_{2}^{+}e^{2ikx_{2}}+H.C.)\nonumber \\
 & =\hbar\frac{\Omega_{eff}(t)}{2}\left(\begin{array}{cc}
0 & e^{2ikx_{1}}+e^{2ikx_{2}}\\
e^{-2ikx_{1}}+e^{-2ikx_{2}} & 0
\end{array}\right)\nonumber \\
 & =\hbar\frac{\Omega_{eff}(t)}{2}(\sigma_{1x}e^{2ikx_{1}\sigma_{1z}}+\sigma_{2x}e^{2ikx_{2}\sigma_{2z}}),
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{c,s}$
\end_inset

 are the frequencies of Center-Of-Mass mode (COM) and Stretch Mode (SM),
 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{c,s}^{+},a_{c,s}$
\end_inset

 is the form and annihilation operation for the corresponding mode, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{ix,z}$
\end_inset

 is the Pauli operation of the ith ion.
 Now we consider the special situation for the scheme: 1.
 
\begin_inset Formula $kx_{1,2}\ll1$
\end_inset

 is not satisfied, which means Lamb-Dicke expansion can not works here;
 2.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau\ll\frac{2\pi}{w_{trap}}$
\end_inset

 , which means the single kick operation time 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

 is much faster than than the trap period.
 So when consider the evolution of the system during a single operation,
 we don't need to consider the effect of 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{m}$
\end_inset

.
 Then if we generate a 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{\pi}}$
\end_inset

 ARP pulse: 
\begin_inset Formula $\int\frac{\Omega_{eff}(t)}{2}dt=\pi/2$
\end_inset

, then the Unitary evolution after the operation can be written as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
U & =e^{\frac{i}{\hbar}\int H_{I}(t)dt}\nonumber \\
 & =e^{i\pi/2(\sigma_{1x}e^{2ikx_{1}\sigma_{1z}}+\sigma_{2x}e^{2ikx_{2}\sigma_{2z}})}\nonumber \\
 & =\sigma_{1x}\sigma_{2x}e^{2ikx_{1}\sigma_{1z}}e^{2ikx_{2}\sigma_{2z}},
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename /Users/apple/Documents/GitHub/Fastgate/kick/fig/fidelity_4.pdf
	scale 45

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:kick"

\end_inset

 Feasibility of the two qubits ultrafast entanglement gate scheme.
 (a) plots phase space trajectory in the rotation frame of COM and SM.
 The blue curves consider ideal condition and the cyan curve consider limited
 single flipping operation (0.5 ns) and infidelity during the single flipping
 (
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-4}$
\end_inset

).
 Parameters are optimized separately for ideal condition.
 (b) shows the the whole entanglement gate fidelity verses single flipping
 duration.
 The gate fidelity is limited by the kick operation time and fidelity.
 The dash line corresponds to the threshold for the proposal determined
 by the flipping error.
 (c) search parameter in laser intensity and flipping time 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

 space to reach high fidelity single flipping.
 Ultrafast and high fidelity operation could be reached with increasing
 the laser intensity.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
with the formula 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{i\theta\sigma\cdot n}=\cos(\theta)I+\sin(\theta)\sigma\cdot n$
\end_inset

.
 Notice that the evolution could be understood as state-dependent momentum
 kick accompanied by the internal state flipping.
 In order to realize the ideal control phase gate, the number of kicks once
 should be even to return the original state.
 In GZC proposal, symmetries pulse sequence gives as shown in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:EightEnergyLevel"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(a):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
t & =[-t_{3},-t_{2},-t_{1},t_{1},t_{2},t_{3}]\\
n & =[2n,-3n,2n,-2n,3n,-2n]\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So under the ideal situation (kicks are all instant without consider the
 repetition rate of the pulses and operation infidelity), the momentum transferr
ing gives the form of:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Delta p(t)=\Sigma_{i=1}^{N}\delta(t-t_{i})4\hbar n_{i}k
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where N is the total number of the kick operations, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}$
\end_inset

 ith kick moment and 
\begin_inset Formula $2n_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the number of state flipping during ith kick (notice every flipping
 could give 
\begin_inset Formula $2\hbar k$
\end_inset

 momentum transferring).
 The ions will experience free evolution between two kicks.
 So we want the final Unitary operation has the form of:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
U_{F}=e^{i\pi/4\sigma_{1z}\sigma_{2z}}e^{-i\tau(\omega_{c}a_{c}^{+}a_{c}+\omega_{s}a_{s}^{+}a_{s})}.
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The gate fidelity is given in the Ref.
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "bentley2015trapped"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{0}=\frac{1}{12}\left(6+e^{-4m|\Delta x|^{2}}+e^{-4m|\Delta y|^{2}}+4e^{-m\left(|\Delta x|^{2}+|\Delta y|^{2}\right)}\cos\left(\theta^{'}\right)\right)$
\end_inset

, where m is the heat distribution before the gate, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta^{'}$
\end_inset

 is phase accumulated after the gate and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x,y$
\end_inset

 are the 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{gather}
\Theta=4\eta^{2}\sum_{m=2}^{N}\sum_{i=1}^{m-1}n_{m}n_{k}\left[\sin(\omega_{c}(t_{m}-t_{i}))-\frac{\sin(\omega_{s}(t_{m}-t_{i}))}{\sqrt{3}}\right]=\frac{\pi}{4}\nonumber \\
\sum_{i=1}^{N}n_{k}e^{-iw_{c}t_{i}}=0\nonumber \\
\sum_{i=1}^{N}n_{k}e^{-iw_{s}t_{i}}=0
\end{gather}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the optimization target can be required as: desired phase accumulated
 equals to 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/4$
\end_inset

 after the whole gate and restoring the motional state of each mode after
 the whole gate.
 Then sequence time 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1,2,3}$
\end_inset

 could be optimized to achieve the high fidelity gate.
 The phase space trajectory of the optimized COM and SM are plotted in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:kick"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(a) with 
\begin_inset Formula $n=5$
\end_inset

 corresponding to 70 kicks in optimized 450 ns with gate infidelity 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{0}$
\end_inset

 higher than 
\begin_inset Formula $1-10^{-7}$
\end_inset

.
 The plots are in the rotation frame (at the frequency of the corresponding
 mode), so the momentum kicks are straight line while changing direction
 for next kick with free evolution between two kicks.
 The cyan curve is for the ideal condition while the blue curve simulate
 real condition for single flipping duration equalling to 0.5 ns.
 Without the limit of the gate repetition rate, the ideal condition could
 be optimized to reach entanglement ultrahigh gate fidelity.
 In our scheme, as shown in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:EightEnergyLevel"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(a), sequence times could shifted by the finite kick time from optimized
 values to cancel the operation time.
 We could further consider the limits of our scheme in the detail.
 The first one is the limited single flipping time.
 In one way, decreasing the single flipping duration will need the linear
 increasing the required laser intensity as shown in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:kick"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(c).
 The linear kick in the momentum space is not a good approximation when
 kick is slow.
 From another point of view, the AWG sampling rate is limited, which could
 not satisfies for the requirement for too fast modulation.
 The second limit is the single kick or flipping fidelity.
 In ref.
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "gale2019optimised"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, the gate infidelity with the imperfect 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{\pi}}$
\end_inset

flipping is given as 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon=4N\epsilon_{0}F_{0}$
\end_inset

, where N represents for the total pulse pairs number during the gate and
 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{0}$
\end_inset

 means single flipping error.
 As in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:kick"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(b) and (c), with increasing the single flipping duration, the gate would
 reach it's limit setting by the imperfect 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{\pi}}$
\end_inset

flipping.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{0}=5\times10^{-5}$
\end_inset

 with single kick error around 
\begin_inset Formula $5\times10^{-4}$
\end_inset

 could be reached in the simulation (Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:kick"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(c) and Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:fidelity"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

(b)) with the total gate fidelity lower than 99.6%.
 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-6}$
\end_inset

 or lower gate infidelity are required for the gate fidelity higher than
 99.9%.
\end_layout

